{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/bash/3-functions/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Rahul's Blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"6e2a33cc-95ac-5eb3-aecc-5628ef1fd510","excerpt":"","html":"<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token shebang important\">#!/bin/bash</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function-name function\">getDate</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">date</span> <span class=\"token comment\"># get current date and time</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># returns an exit status number between 0-255</span>\n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">return</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\ngetDate\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">#global variable</span>\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">name</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Rahul\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">#local values aren't available outside of the function</span>\n<span class=\"token function-name function\">demLocal</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">local</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">name</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Titu\"</span>\n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">return</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\ndemLocal\n\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$name</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># a function that receives 2 values and returns a sum</span>\n<span class=\"token function-name function\">getSum</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># attributes are retrieved by referring $1, $2 ..etc</span>\n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">local</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">num3</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\">$1</span> \n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">local</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">num4</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\">$2</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">local</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">sum</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$((</span>num3<span class=\"token operator\">+</span>num4<span class=\"token variable\">))</span></span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">#pass values back with echo</span>\n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$sum</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">num1</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token number\">4</span>\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">num2</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token number\">9</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># pass attributes by seperating them with a space</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\"># surround function call with $() to get the return value</span>\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">sum</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>getSum num1 num2<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"the sum is <span class=\"token variable\">$sum</span>\"</span></code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Bash Shell Scripting: Functions","date":"July 21, 2020","description":"learn how to declare and use functions in bash shell scripting. How to pass parameters/attributes in function and how to access them?"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/bash/3-functions/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/bash/12-value-seperator/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Bash Shell Scripting: Value seperator in strings"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/bash/1-variables/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Bash Shell Scripting: Variables"}}}}}